-♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS ♪

01:43.712 --> 01:46.671
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE.

02:12.436 --> 02:14.090
♪

02:46.818 --> 02:48.255
-WELL, THE WAVE RUNNER'S
HERE, BUT...

02:49.038 --> 02:49.908
WHERE'S EVERYBODY ELSE?

02:50.474 --> 02:51.823
I DON'T KNOW,

02:51.954 --> 02:53.042
MAYBE THEY DIDN'T COME.
COME ON, LET'S GO.

02:53.173 --> 02:54.391
-NO, NO. WAIT A SECOND.

02:55.131 --> 02:57.002
THORPE TOLD ME
THE BOARD OF SUPERVISORS
WAS GONNA BE HERE.

02:57.133 --> 02:58.526
.WELL, THEY'RE NOT.
SO COME ON, LET'S GO.

02:59.222 --> 03:01.398
LOOK AT THAT GUY
BRINGING THAT ADDICTOR
CLOSE TO SHORE.

03:02.051 --> 03:03.487
-PLEASE?

03:03.618 --> 03:06.795
-HEY! GET THAT THING OUT
BEYOND THE SURF LINE.

03:07.883 --> 03:09.058
NOW!

03:09.189 --> 03:10.755
-WHOA!

03:10.886 --> 03:11.843
-DAMN IT!

03:16.544 --> 03:17.675
-DAD, DONT!
-RIDER: HELP!

03:17.806 --> 03:18.894
-PLEASE, DON'T GO
OUT THERE.

03:19.024 --> 03:20.200
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
LET GO.

03:20.330 --> 03:21.723
-DAD, PLEASE DON'T
GO OUT THERE.

03:21.853 --> 03:22.680
-WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?
-DON'T GO OUT THERE.

03:22.811 --> 03:24.029
-LET GO OF ME.

03:24.160 --> 03:25.857
-COME ON, DAD.
DON'T GO OUT THERE.

03:25.988 --> 03:28.512
-RIDER: HELP, HELP!
-DAD, COME BACK.

03:31.776 --> 03:32.951
-AH!

03:33.082 --> 03:34.475
-PLEASE DON'T
GO OUT THERE.

03:43.223 --> 03:44.354
-HELP!

03:56.975 --> 03:57.846
-DAD!

04:03.155 --> 04:04.244
DIVE DOWN!

04:09.640 --> 04:11.512
DAD!

04:13.644 --> 04:14.428
-HOBIE.

04:14.558 --> 04:15.646
-DAD, YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

04:16.386 --> 04:17.648
-YEAH, OF COURSE.

04:17.779 --> 04:19.259
I'M OKAY, IT'S JUST
A DREAM.

04:20.084 --> 04:21.391
I WAS SO SCARED.

04:21.522 --> 04:24.829
-[SIGHS] IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY.

04:25.917 --> 04:27.658
JUST A BAD DREAM,
THAT'S ALL.

04:33.185 --> 04:35.623
-I KEPT CALLING TO YOU,
BUT YOU COULDN'T HEAR ME.

04:36.276 --> 04:38.669
IT WAS COMING RIGHT AT YOU.
IT SEEMED SO REAL.

04:39.714 --> 04:41.150
-WHAT COLOR
WAS THE WAVE RUNNER?

04:41.281 --> 04:42.282
-YELLOW.

04:42.891 --> 04:43.718
-YELLOW.

04:44.893 --> 04:46.155
THE COLOR
OF RESCUE VEHICLES.

04:46.286 --> 04:47.591
-YEAH.

04:47.722 --> 04:48.940
-HEY, HOLD IT, SIR.

04:49.637 --> 04:51.378
LAST NIGHT BEFORE
WE WENT TO BED,

04:51.987 --> 04:55.773
WEREN'T WE TALKING
ABOUT USING WAVE RUNNERS
AS RESCUE VEHICLES?

04:55.904 --> 04:58.472
-DON'T GET THEM, DAD.
SOMETHING BAD WILL HAPPEN
IF YOU DO.

04:58.602 --> 05:00.038
-OH, HOBIE.

05:00.778 --> 05:01.997
-I'M SERIOUS, DAD.

05:03.651 --> 05:04.913
IT SAYS IN THIS BOOK

05:05.479 --> 05:06.958
THAT SOME DREAMS
ARE PREMONITIONS,

05:07.089 --> 05:08.786
LIKE WARNINGS
NOT TO DO STUFF.

05:08.917 --> 05:11.180
AND THIS WAS ONE, I KNOW IT.

05:11.311 --> 05:14.314
-I KNOW YOUR DREAMS
SEEM REAL, BUT IT WAS JUST
A SCARY DREAM. THAT'S ALL.

05:14.444 --> 05:15.880
-BUT DREAMS CAN COME TRUE.

05:16.011 --> 05:18.143
-I'M NOT GONNA GET
RUN DOWN BY A JET SKI.

05:18.274 --> 05:20.058
TRUST ME.

05:20.189 --> 05:22.147
NOW COME ON, FINISH YOUR CEREAL.
WE GOT A BIG DAY AHEAD OF US.

05:26.326 --> 05:28.110
-[BOTH GIGGLING]
-I KNOW.

05:28.240 --> 05:29.851
-MITCH, I'VE BEEN ROUND
AND AROUND WITH THE COUNTY
ON THIS.

05:29.981 --> 05:31.809
THEY STILL THINK IT'S
AN UNNECESSARY EXPENDITURE.

05:31.940 --> 05:33.637
-I'M TELLING YOU,
WAVE RUNNERS CAN SAVE LIVES.

05:33.768 --> 05:35.422
-THEORETICALLY.
-DEFINITELY.

05:36.292 --> 05:38.599
JUST GET ME A DEMONSTRATION,
THAT'S ALL I ASK.

05:38.729 --> 05:41.036
-YOU MEAN YOU EXPECT THEM
TO COME DOWN HERE AND GET
SAND IN THEIR SHOES?

05:41.166 --> 05:43.299
-BETTER THAN BETWEEN THEIR EARS,
WHERE IT IS NOW.

05:43.430 --> 05:46.128
LOOK, WE GET THE FACTORY
TO OUTPUT A PROTOTYPE,

05:46.258 --> 05:48.217
NO EXPENSE TO THE COUNTY.

05:48.348 --> 05:50.828
WE SET UP A MOCK RESCUE
AND SHOW THEM WHAT WAVE RUNNERS
CAN REALLY DO.

05:51.394 --> 05:52.874
-YOU REALLY FEEL VERY STRONGLY
ABOUT THIS, DON'T YOU?

05:53.004 --> 05:55.311
-ABSOLUTELY.

05:55.442 --> 05:57.879
ONE WAVE RUNNER CAN TAKE
THREE GUARDS TO A RESCUE
IN A QUARTER OF THE TIME.

05:58.009 --> 06:01.099
OR LET ONE GUARD BRING IN
TWO VICTIMS WITHOUT HAVING
TO SWIM THEM THROUGH THE SURF.

06:01.230 --> 06:02.318
-SOUNDS LIKE A DREAM.

06:03.232 --> 06:04.799
-YOU BEEN TALKING TO HOBIE?
-HOBIE? NO, WHY?

06:05.495 --> 06:07.715
-NEVER MIND, JUST
GET ME THE DEMO.

06:07.845 --> 06:09.238
-[SIGHS] NO PROMISES.

06:09.369 --> 06:13.329
BUT I'LL, UH...
I'LL DO MY BEST.

06:13.851 --> 06:15.636
-THANKS.
-[ENGINE STARTS]

06:21.206 --> 06:22.686
♪

06:47.407 --> 06:50.758
♪ I FEEL THE HEAT, YOU'RE SO SWEET

06:50.888 --> 06:53.804
♪ YOU KNOW YOU BLOW ME AWAY

06:54.675 --> 06:58.418
♪ COME ON NOW, I'M GONNA SHOW YOU HOW ♪

06:58.548 --> 07:01.246
♪ YOU'RE GONNA MAKE MY DAY

07:02.683 --> 07:04.772
♪ HOT NIGHTS

07:04.902 --> 07:07.209
♪ SUGAR AND SPICE

07:08.210 --> 07:11.039
♪ YOU GOT ME SPINNING

07:11.169 --> 07:14.477
♪ INTO A DREAM

07:16.087 --> 07:19.569
♪ BURN IT UP YOU MAKE IT LOOK EASY

07:19.700 --> 07:22.746
♪ SETTING FIRE TO THE SKY

07:22.877 --> 07:27.447
-♪ TURN IT UP YOU SHAKE IT TO TEASE ME

07:27.577 --> 07:30.275
♪ YOU DON'T EVEN HAVE TO TRY

07:33.017 --> 07:34.715
-♪ YOU TAKE MY BREATH AWAY

07:36.586 --> 07:39.241
♪ WISH YOU WERE HERE TO STAY

07:40.547 --> 07:42.549
♪ A PRETTY PRICE TO PAY

07:44.420 --> 07:46.857
♪ YOU TAKE MY BREATH AWAY

07:48.206 --> 07:50.774
♪ WISH YOU WERE HERE TO STAY

08:26.331 --> 08:27.985
-♪ YOU TAKE MY BREATH AWAY

08:30.118 --> 08:32.511
♪ WISH YOU WERE HERE TO STAY

08:33.904 --> 08:37.429
♪ YOU TAKE MY BREATH AWAY

08:44.261 --> 08:45.307
-LET ME GUESS.

08:46.787 --> 08:49.180
THE REDHEAD ON THE ROLLERBLADES.

08:49.311 --> 08:50.181
-NOPE.

08:52.270 --> 08:53.271
-WHAT, SOME KIND
OF PROBLEM?

08:55.273 --> 08:56.797
-I'M AFRAID SOMEBODY DIED.

08:58.581 --> 08:59.451
-WHERE?

09:00.757 --> 09:02.890
-ON THE GOLD COAST,
THE OLD JAMES HOUSE.

09:06.676 --> 09:08.809
-BEN, NO ONE'S LIVED
IN THAT HOUSE FOR 20 YEARS.

09:08.939 --> 09:09.940
-31.

09:10.811 --> 09:13.553
MAGGIE JAMES WAS LIVING
AS A RECLUSE IN NEW ENGLAND.

09:15.293 --> 09:16.643
SHE DIDN'T SELL IT,
DIDN'T RENT IT.

09:17.295 --> 09:19.080
SO IF SOMEBODY NEW
IS MOVING IN,

09:20.168 --> 09:21.473
SHE MUST HAVE PASSED AWAY.

09:25.739 --> 09:28.132
-THAT'S TOO BAD.

09:28.263 --> 09:30.700
-MAGGIE JAMES WAS THE MOST
BEAUTIFUL WOMAN THAT EVER
GRACED THE SILVER SCREEN.

09:32.702 --> 09:35.313
SHE WAS MORE PROVOCATIVE
THAN VERONICA LAKE,

09:35.444 --> 09:37.228
MORE ELEGANT THAN GRACE KELLY,

09:38.229 --> 09:39.535
TOUGHER THAN BETTE DAVIS.

09:41.798 --> 09:43.060
-WOW.

09:43.670 --> 09:46.194
-HER LAST YEAR IN THAT HOUSE
WAS MY ROOKIE YEAR ON THE BEACH.

09:47.848 --> 09:48.675
-DID YOU GET TO KNOW HER?

09:50.154 --> 09:51.199
-SADLY, NO.

09:52.592 --> 09:55.856
I JUST WATCHED HER FROM AFAR
LIKE A LOVESICK FOOL.

09:55.986 --> 09:57.858
-I DON'T BELIEVE THAT
FOR A MINUTE.

09:58.380 --> 09:59.860
NOT THE LEGENDARY BEN EDWARDS.

10:01.339 --> 10:04.691
THOUGHT YOU DATED EVERY
STARLET WHO CAME WITHIN
WALKING DISTANCE OF YOUR TOWER.

10:05.343 --> 10:06.214
-STARLET?

10:07.911 --> 10:09.521
MAGGIE JAMES
WAS A STAR.

10:42.163 --> 10:43.686
♪

11:31.821 --> 11:33.475
-HEY, IT'S ME.

11:33.605 --> 11:35.390
LISTEN, I'M GONNA BE DONE
IN ABOUT TEN MINUTES

11:35.520 --> 11:37.609
SO WHY DON'T YOU
MEET ME HERE, WE'LL DO
A LITTLE WORKOUT,

11:37.740 --> 11:39.176
AND THEN GO GET
SOMETHING TO EAT.

12:17.040 --> 12:18.302
-YEAH, I KNOW.

12:18.912 --> 12:20.043
WORKING VENICE IS WEIRD.

12:20.174 --> 12:21.436
GET THIS ONE,
THIS IS CLASSIC.

12:22.176 --> 12:23.655
SOME CULT WAS DOWN HERE EARLIER,

12:23.786 --> 12:25.701
DRAWING CIRCLES IN THE SAND

12:25.832 --> 12:27.703
SO THE SPACESHIPS COULD SEE
WHERE TO PICK THEM UP.

12:27.834 --> 12:29.357
AND THOSE ARE
THE SANE ONES.

12:45.112 --> 12:46.504
WHEW.

12:46.635 --> 12:49.377
YOU KNOW, IT SURE IS
GETTING HOT IN HERE.

12:50.334 --> 12:51.858
-[SIGHS]
-[KNOCKING]

12:54.643 --> 12:58.821
-UH, SHAUNI,
I THINK MY TOWER IS ON FIRE.

12:58.952 --> 13:00.214
CALL IT IN, WOULD YA?

13:06.046 --> 13:08.396
[COUGHING]

13:22.889 --> 13:25.326
HEY!
GET OUT OF THERE!

13:25.456 --> 13:27.197
WHAT, ARE YOU CRAZY?
YOU'RE GONNA BURN YOURSELF.

13:27.328 --> 13:28.503
HEY!

13:40.558 --> 13:43.344
-SUMO! SUMO! SUMO!

13:45.215 --> 13:46.913
SUMO!

14:15.332 --> 14:16.638
-CONNORS TOOK HIM IN.

14:17.291 --> 14:19.380
LET ME TELL YOU, THIS CRAZY
WAS SUCKING UP TOO MANY FUMES.

14:19.902 --> 14:22.296
EDDIE, I KNOW SCORCH. HE'S BEEN
WORKING THE STRAND FOR YEARS.

14:22.426 --> 14:23.819
HE'S NOT CRAZY.

14:23.950 --> 14:25.908
-MITCH, THE MAN EATS FIRE.
HE IS CRAZY.

14:26.039 --> 14:28.215
-SO HE COOKS HIS FOOD
AFTER HE SWALLOWS IT,
BIG DEAL.

14:28.737 --> 14:30.086
-MITCH, THE GUY
BURNED DOWN MY TOWER.

14:30.217 --> 14:31.392
-YEAH, I KNOW.

14:31.914 --> 14:33.742
-CONNORS THINKS SCORCH
GOT A HOLD OF SOME BAD DRUGS.

14:36.223 --> 14:37.441
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

14:37.572 --> 14:38.921
-YOUR HAIR GOT A LITTLE SINGED.

14:55.982 --> 14:57.374
-DON'T TOUCH THAT!

14:59.899 --> 15:01.770
-MISS, MISS JAMES!

15:03.467 --> 15:04.555
YOU'RE ALIVE!

15:04.686 --> 15:06.557
-DO I LOOK LIKE
A GHOST TO YOU?

15:06.688 --> 15:08.385
-NO! NO, NOT AT ALL.

15:09.952 --> 15:11.911
-THEN I'M STILL
FLESH AND BLOOD.

15:19.962 --> 15:21.268
WHO ARE YOU?

15:21.398 --> 15:22.617
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

15:22.747 --> 15:25.359
-UM, MY NAME IS
BEN EDWARDS, MA'AM.

15:25.489 --> 15:26.621
I'M AN L.A. COUNTY
LIFEGUARD.

15:30.059 --> 15:32.235
I MAKE UP FOR THIS
WITH EXPERIENCE.

15:32.366 --> 15:34.150
MAY I SAY, MISS JAMES,
THAT YOU...

15:34.759 --> 15:36.718
YOU'RE JUST AS--
NO YOU'RE MORE BEAUTIFUL
THAN EVER.

15:37.806 --> 15:39.242
-YOU MAY, BUT I DON'T
BELIEVE IT.

15:40.809 --> 15:42.637
HOWEVER, I LOVE COMPLIMENTS.

15:43.420 --> 15:44.595
YOU MUST BE THIRSTY.

15:44.726 --> 15:46.075
-YES, MA'AM.
I'M DRY AS A BONE.

15:59.654 --> 16:01.221
BEN:
OH, MAN.

16:14.016 --> 16:19.369
-THIS HOUSE WAS SO ALIVE
BEFORE I LEFT IT.

16:20.718 --> 16:22.024
ALWAYS A PARTY.

16:22.546 --> 16:23.895
ALWAYS VISITORS.

16:24.853 --> 16:27.987
AND WHEN I SEE IT IN
MY MIND'S EYE, IN MY MEMORY,

16:28.857 --> 16:31.164
I'M ALWAYS ALONE
AT SUNSET.

16:32.992 --> 16:34.254
THOUGH,
I DON'T THINK I EVER WAS.

16:36.604 --> 16:37.822
-[CLEARS THROAT] THANK YOU.

16:38.432 --> 16:39.999
YOU KNOW, I WONDERED
ABOUT THAT--

16:40.129 --> 16:42.697
-DON'T ASK ME QUESTIONS
OR YOU SHALL HAVE TO LEAVE.

16:42.827 --> 16:43.872
-OH, I'M SORRY.

16:44.003 --> 16:45.961
-NEVER APOLOGIZE.

16:46.962 --> 16:48.268
NO REGRETS.

16:48.398 --> 16:50.139
THAT'S THE SECRET OF LIFE.

16:55.362 --> 16:56.363
TURN SIDEWAYS.

16:59.583 --> 17:01.368
FINE, BE STUBBORN.

17:07.852 --> 17:11.551
DID YOU WORK AS A LIFEGUARD
IN THE SUMMER OF '62?

17:11.682 --> 17:13.510
-I THOUGHT YOU SAID
QUESTIONS WERE NOT ALLOWED.

17:13.641 --> 17:15.208
-BY YOU, NOT ME.

17:15.338 --> 17:16.557
-OH, NO.

17:16.686 --> 17:19.255
YOU ANSWER MY QUESTIONS,
I ANSWER YOURS.

17:19.907 --> 17:22.650
NOW WHY DID YOU COME BACK
HERE AFTER BEING AWAY
FOR 30 YEARS?

17:24.478 --> 17:25.305
-WELL, I...

17:26.696 --> 17:30.875
I FINALLY REALIZED THAT
I NEVER SHOULD HAVE LEFT IT
AT ALL.

17:31.006 --> 17:31.876
-YES.

17:32.007 --> 17:33.617
-I BEG YOUR PARDON.

17:34.270 --> 17:37.447
-SUMMER '62, I OFTEN
WORKED THE TOWER
RIGHT ACROSS FROM YOUR HOUSE.

17:39.188 --> 17:40.059
-SOME MORE SHERRY?

17:42.278 --> 17:43.453
-DO YOU HAVE
ANY BEER?

17:43.975 --> 17:46.369
-NO, I CERTAINLY DO NOT.

17:47.936 --> 17:49.546
-MAYBE JUST A LITTLE, PLEASE.

18:07.216 --> 18:08.261
-BOY: CHECK IT OUT!

18:09.784 --> 18:10.741
WOW!

18:12.787 --> 18:13.701
-GIRL:
WHAT HAPPENED?

18:19.924 --> 18:21.100
-EW.

18:21.926 --> 18:23.102
-DON'T TOUCH IT.

18:36.202 --> 18:38.856
-ALL RIGHT, I'LL ASK MITCH
TO KEEP EVERYONE OUT
OF THE WATER.

18:39.857 --> 18:41.642
BUT IN THE MEAN TIME,
YOU GET BACK TO ME

18:41.772 --> 18:42.904
AND LET ME KNOW WHY
THOSE FISH DIED AS SOON
AS POSSIBLE.

18:44.210 --> 18:45.820
-WHOO, THIS PLACE STINKS.

18:45.950 --> 18:47.517
-I DON'T SMELL ANYTHING, DO YOU?

18:47.648 --> 18:49.084
-NO. [SNIFFS]

18:49.998 --> 18:52.218
BUT, CONNORS, YOU SMELL
LIKE DEAD FISH. YOU OUGHT TO TRY
A DIFFERENT DEODORANT.

18:53.480 --> 18:55.090
SO WHAT'S UP,
WHAT DO YOU GOT?

18:55.221 --> 18:56.961
-YOU KNOW THAT FIRE-EATER
THAT TORCHED YOUR TOWER?

18:58.049 --> 19:00.356
HE WAS WHACKED OUT
ON SOMETHING CALLED SPICE.

19:00.487 --> 19:01.792
-SPICE, WHAT'S THAT?

19:01.923 --> 19:03.881
-WELL, IT'S SOME NEW
DESIGNER DRUG

19:04.012 --> 19:06.319
AND THIS STUFF'S LIKE
DANCING WITH DEATH.

19:06.449 --> 19:09.626
YOU KNOW, WE CAME THIS CLOSE
TO SHUTTING DOWN OUR WHOLE
OPERATION LAST MONTH.

19:09.757 --> 19:10.845
-WHAT HAPPENED?

19:11.367 --> 19:13.543
-WELL, WE GOT TO THE LAB
ABOUT AN HOUR TOO LATE.

19:13.674 --> 19:16.633
NOW THEY'VE SET IT UP SOMEPLACE
ELSE, BUT WE HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE
TO FIND 'EM YET.

19:16.764 --> 19:17.852
-WAIT A MINUTE.

19:18.983 --> 19:19.897
WAIT A MINUTE,

19:20.028 --> 19:21.290
THAT CRAZY KEPT...

19:22.073 --> 19:24.337
WELL, HE KEPT SAYING,
"SUMO, SUMO."

19:24.946 --> 19:26.600
MAYBE THERE'S SOMETHING THERE.

19:26.730 --> 19:28.341
-LIKE WHAT? LIKE HE GOT IT
FROM SOME BIG FAT WRESTLER.

19:28.471 --> 19:29.994
-I DON'T KNOW.

19:30.125 --> 19:31.300
I DON'T KNOW, THAT'S JUST
WHAT HE KEPT SAYING.

19:47.360 --> 19:49.710
-DAD, CAN'T YOU JUST CANCEL
THE DEMONSTRATION?

19:49.840 --> 19:50.667
-NOPE.

19:52.103 --> 19:54.541
-THEN CAN YOU GET
SOMEBODY ELSE TO DO IT?

19:54.671 --> 19:58.458
-HOBIE, I'M GONNA DO THIS
AND PROVE TO YOU, YOU DON'T HAVE
TO BE AFRAID OF YOUR DREAMS.

19:58.588 --> 19:59.459
-DAD!

19:59.589 --> 20:01.243
-WHAT?

20:01.374 --> 20:03.071
-THAT JOGGER, IT'S THE SAME ONE
THAT WAS IN MY DREAM.

20:04.028 --> 20:05.639
-COME ON, PAL.

20:05.769 --> 20:07.945
-NO, REALLY. IT RAN PAST
THE TRUCK JUST LIKE THAT.

20:08.076 --> 20:10.121
I SWEAR, I AM NOT
MAKING IT UP.

20:11.645 --> 20:12.646
IT'S "DIJA-VIEW."

20:12.776 --> 20:14.125
-WHAT?

20:14.778 --> 20:16.345
-YOU KNOW, WHERE YOU'RE SEEING
SOMETHING YOU'VE SEEN BEFORE.

20:16.476 --> 20:17.564
-"DIJA-VIEW."

20:18.129 --> 20:19.740
-DEJA VU.

20:19.870 --> 20:21.655
-I KNOW, SO DON'T GO OUT
ON THE WAVE RUNNER TODAY.

20:22.612 --> 20:24.919
-HOBIE, EVERYTHING'S
GONNA BE FINE. DON'T WORRY.

20:25.049 --> 20:26.529
-THAT'S WHAT LINCOLN SAID.

20:26.660 --> 20:28.531
-LINCOLN? LINCOLN WHO?

20:28.662 --> 20:29.663
-ABE LINCOLN.

20:30.620 --> 20:32.405
BEFORE HE GOT SHOT.

20:32.535 --> 20:34.885
HE HAD A DREAM ABOUT IT,
BUT HE DIDN'T PAY
ATTENTION TO IT.

20:40.021 --> 20:42.153
[FAST ROCK BEAT PLAYING]

21:15.230 --> 21:18.277
♪ I'M GONNA FLY FLY FLY

21:20.496 --> 21:23.760
♪ I GOT THE WIND IN MY SAIL

21:29.200 --> 21:32.465
♪ I'M GONNA DRIVE DRIVE DRIVE

21:34.118 --> 21:37.774
♪ I GET THAT MOTOR TO WAIL

21:43.954 --> 21:48.263
♪ YEAH WE'RE FLYIN IN THE SUN

21:50.874 --> 21:55.357
♪ YEAH WE'LL FLY TILL THE DAY IS DONE

22:12.069 --> 22:14.594
♪ I'M GONNA RIDE RIDE RIDE

22:16.857 --> 22:20.251
♪ I'M GONNA TAKE WHAT I WANT

22:26.170 --> 22:30.261
♪ YEAH WE'RE FLYIN IN THE SUN

22:31.219 --> 22:33.874
♪ SUN SUN SUN SUN SUN

22:34.788 --> 22:37.399
♪ SUN SUN SUN SUN SUN

22:41.838 --> 22:44.363
♪ SUN SUN SUN SUN SUN

22:47.627 --> 22:48.715
-NOT BAD!

23:20.442 --> 23:21.748
-WHATCHA DOIN' UP THERE?

23:21.878 --> 23:24.403
-TOP OF THE WORLD, MITCHY BOY.

23:24.968 --> 23:25.969
[LAUGHS]

23:27.667 --> 23:28.755
[MITCH SIGHS]

23:29.625 --> 23:30.757
WHAT'S GOTTEN INTO YOU?

23:30.887 --> 23:33.194
-SHERRY. [LAUGHS]

23:33.977 --> 23:35.805
IN TEENY, TINY GLASSES.

23:37.633 --> 23:42.812
IT'S THE MOST REVOLTING LIQUID
THAT HAS COME OUT OF
A PERFECTLY GOOD GRAPE.

23:44.379 --> 23:46.947
-HOW MANY OF THOSE
TEENY, TINY GLASSES
DID YOU HAVE?

23:47.077 --> 23:48.165
-TWO.

23:48.775 --> 23:50.429
BUT I BROKE ONE.
[LAUGHS]

23:52.169 --> 23:54.563
MAGGIE, SHE CALLED ME
A CLUMSY OAF.

23:55.172 --> 23:56.043
-MAGGIE?

23:57.436 --> 23:59.699
YOU MEAN MAGGIE JAMES?
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
SHE WAS DEAD.

23:59.829 --> 24:02.832
-THAT'S HOW RUMORS START, MITCH.

24:02.963 --> 24:04.399
-YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO TOLD ME.

24:04.530 --> 24:06.793
-HAPPILY, I WAS
MISINFORMED.

24:08.925 --> 24:11.754
SHE IS STILL BEAUTIFUL, MITCH.

24:14.627 --> 24:16.672
AND THE WOMAN
BREATHES FIRE.

24:16.803 --> 24:18.108
[MITCH SIGHS]

24:18.718 --> 24:19.980
-SO DO YOU.

24:20.110 --> 24:21.721
-WHEN I LEFT HER,

24:22.678 --> 24:26.552
I FELT SOMETHING THAT
I HADN'T FELT IN YEARS.

24:27.553 --> 24:28.336
-PLASTERED?

24:28.467 --> 24:29.729
-BOILING.

24:29.859 --> 24:31.208
-BOILING?

24:31.339 --> 24:32.471
-LIKE A VOLCANO.

24:33.689 --> 24:36.692
IT'S BEEN DORMANT
FOR A VERY LONG TIME.

24:39.347 --> 24:40.261
-YOU KNOW, BEN,

24:41.001 --> 24:41.915
YOU'RE STILL MY IDOL.

24:44.352 --> 24:45.222
COME ON, I'LL HELP YOU DOWN.

24:45.353 --> 24:48.443
-NO, MY GOOD FRIEND. NO.

24:49.488 --> 24:53.492
I WANT TO STAY OUT HERE
AND WATCH THIS BEAUTIFUL VIEW.

24:54.318 --> 24:55.189
-ALL RIGHT.

24:56.146 --> 24:56.973
-JUST DON'T ERUPT.

24:57.104 --> 24:58.801
[BOTH LAUGH]

25:15.688 --> 25:17.646
-WHAT? THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

25:17.777 --> 25:19.518
-THE TEST RESULTS
ARE RIGHT HERE. READ THEM
FOR YOURSELF.

25:20.301 --> 25:22.608
YOU KNOW, I'VE HEARD OF PUTTING
SPICE ON FISH, BUT NEVER TO THE
POINT WHERE THEY O.D.'D.

25:23.130 --> 25:25.567
-THIS IS CRAZY.

25:25.698 --> 25:28.396
HOW COULD A SCHOOL OF FISH
BELLY UP ON THE SAME DRUG
WE FOUND IN THAT FIRE-EATER?

25:28.527 --> 25:31.355
-I GUESS THIS SCHOOL DIDN'T HAVE
A "JUST SAY NO" PROGRAM.

25:31.486 --> 25:33.096
[PHONE RINGS]

25:36.883 --> 25:38.667
-THIS IS A LOGICAL EXPLANATION.

25:38.798 --> 25:40.539
-WHY WOULD ANYBODY
WANT TO DUMP THEIR DRUGS
OFF A BOAT?

25:40.669 --> 25:42.845
-THINK ABOUT IT.

25:42.976 --> 25:44.455
NO FIXED LOCATION,
THEY GET BUSTED, THEY CAN MOVE
WHEREVER THEY WANT.

25:44.586 --> 25:45.848
-AND THEN IF SOMEBODY
FINDS THEM?

25:45.979 --> 25:47.415
-THAT'S RIGHT, THEY DUMP
IT IN THE WATER.

25:47.546 --> 25:49.852
-LET'S CONTACT
THE HARBOR PATROL,

25:49.983 --> 25:51.985
THE COAST GUARD, AND GET A LIST
OF ALL THE BOATS THAT THEY'VE
STOPPED RECENTLY.

25:52.115 --> 25:53.552
-ALL RIGHT. IN THE MEANTIME,
WE SHOULD CHECK OUR OWN
LOGS TOO.

25:53.682 --> 25:54.553
-OKAY.

25:56.337 --> 25:57.294
-[KNOCKING]

26:09.959 --> 26:11.221
-WELL, THEY'RE LOVELY.

26:13.615 --> 26:15.791
I'M SO GLAD
YOU DECIDED TO VISIT AGAIN.

26:16.879 --> 26:19.795
WAITING FOR NOTICES
CAN BE SO NERVE-RACKING.

26:19.926 --> 26:22.406
MAGGIE JAMES WAS A
DYNAMIC PRESENCE

26:22.537 --> 26:24.365
WHO MESMERIZED HER AUDIENCE

26:24.495 --> 26:26.889
WITH HER RARE
AND MAGNIFICENT BEAUTY.

26:27.020 --> 26:27.890
-OH.

26:30.545 --> 26:32.199
I ALWAYS WELCOME
GOOD REVIEWS.

26:32.329 --> 26:34.027
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

26:34.157 --> 26:36.029
-COME IN.
-THANK YOU.

26:38.118 --> 26:41.382
[SLOW, BIG BAND JAZZ PLAYING]

26:41.512 --> 26:43.950
-MADE SOME PASTA.

26:44.080 --> 26:46.126
WELL, IT'S JUST TWO OF US.

26:46.256 --> 26:47.040
-FOR US?

26:47.170 --> 26:49.042
[CHATTERING]

26:57.267 --> 26:59.226
-TO A BEAUTIFUL SUNSET.

26:59.356 --> 27:00.575
-AND A BEAUTIFUL WOMAN.

27:03.752 --> 27:05.624
♪

27:28.647 --> 27:29.865
[LAUGHS]

27:29.996 --> 27:30.953
-WATCH ME.

27:31.084 --> 27:33.086
-[LAUGHING] OH.

27:35.044 --> 27:36.959
♪

27:52.453 --> 27:54.107
-YOU KNOW, I'VE GOT
A GREAT IDEA.

27:54.716 --> 27:56.631
WHY DON'T YOU AND I
TAKE A MIDNIGHT SWIM?

27:58.546 --> 27:59.329
-NO.

27:59.460 --> 28:00.809
-OH, COME ON.

28:00.940 --> 28:02.245
I KNOW I'M A KLUTZ
ON THE DANCE FLOOR,

28:02.376 --> 28:03.986
BUT IN THE WATER
I'M LIKE FRED ASTAIRE.

28:04.117 --> 28:05.248
-I SAID NO.

28:06.075 --> 28:06.902
-BUT WHY NOT?

28:10.123 --> 28:11.733
-THAT IS NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

28:13.779 --> 28:15.606
IT'S LATE, I THINK
YOU'D BETTER LEAVE.

28:16.390 --> 28:17.260
GOOD NIGHT.

28:17.913 --> 28:19.132
-MAGGIE, IF I'VE
SAID SOMETHING--

28:19.262 --> 28:20.263
-NO, PLEASE.

28:21.700 --> 28:23.179
JUST LOCK THE DOOR
ON YOUR WAY OUT.

28:25.225 --> 28:26.095
GOOD NIGHT.

28:28.837 --> 28:30.621
-THANK YOU VERY MUCH
FOR A WONDERFUL EVENING.

28:31.448 --> 28:32.449
I REALLY ENJOYED IT.

29:19.018 --> 29:21.368
-DAD! DAD, WATCH OUT!

29:21.498 --> 29:23.152
[WHIMPERING]

29:23.283 --> 29:24.675
DAD, BEHIND YOU. DAD!

29:24.806 --> 29:26.155
DAD, WATCH OUT.

29:26.286 --> 29:27.504
DAD, WATCH OUT!

29:27.635 --> 29:29.637
DAD! DAD, BEHIND YOU.

29:29.768 --> 29:31.160
-WAKE UP, WAKE UP.
IT'S OKAY, WAKE UP!

29:32.248 --> 29:33.597
-IT WAS THE SAME ONE.

29:33.728 --> 29:35.077
THE SAME DREAM!

29:35.208 --> 29:37.166
-HOBIE, IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY.

29:37.297 --> 29:39.821
-WHY WON'T YOU
LISTEN TO ME?

29:39.952 --> 29:42.258
[CRYING]

29:42.389 --> 29:44.347
-OH, IT'S OKAY.

29:45.087 --> 29:46.132
I'M HERE.

30:11.853 --> 30:12.636
-SHAUNI, LOOK AT THIS.

30:12.767 --> 30:13.681
-WHAT?

30:13.812 --> 30:15.074
-THE NAME OF THIS BOAT.

30:15.204 --> 30:16.336
SUMO.

30:17.467 --> 30:18.817
THAT'S WHAT FIRE BREATH
KEPT SAYING.

30:19.992 --> 30:21.428
AND CHECK THIS OUT,

30:21.558 --> 30:23.517
COAST GUARD INSPECTED
THIS BOAT LAST TUESDAY.

30:24.474 --> 30:25.301
-LET ME SEE THAT.

30:26.781 --> 30:28.000
NO RUNNING LIGHTS
AT NIGHT.

30:28.130 --> 30:29.915
-MM-HMM. I'LL CALL CONNORS.

30:32.569 --> 30:33.832
-NO RUNNING LIGHTS AT NIGHT.

30:47.193 --> 30:48.498
-THAT'S HER SLIP.

30:49.804 --> 30:51.937
-HEY, EXCUSE ME,
HAVE YOU SEEN THE SUMO?

30:52.067 --> 30:54.548
-YEAH, SHE JUST PUT OUT
A COUPLE OF HOURS AGO.

30:58.552 --> 30:59.988
-ONE NIGHT...

31:02.121 --> 31:05.428
31 YEARS AGO,

31:08.736 --> 31:09.650
JEFFREY HOLTZMAN--

31:09.780 --> 31:10.781
-THAT'S THE DIRECTOR.

31:11.913 --> 31:13.610
HE DROWNED HERE ON THIS BEACH.

31:13.741 --> 31:14.655
-YES.

31:16.265 --> 31:17.223
YES, HE DID.

31:20.226 --> 31:21.357
JEFFREY AND I...

31:23.403 --> 31:25.013
WENT FOR A MIDNIGHT SWIM,

31:26.623 --> 31:27.537
TOGETHER.

31:30.627 --> 31:32.151
HE'D BEEN DRINKING. HE...

31:34.153 --> 31:35.806
HE COULDN'T MAKE IT
BACK TO THE SHORE.

31:40.159 --> 31:42.161
I TRIED TO HELP HIM,
BUT I WASN'T STRONG ENOUGH.

31:45.904 --> 31:48.254
WHEN I STAGGERED UP
ONTO THE BEACH,

31:50.169 --> 31:51.605
I PASSED YOUR TOWER.

31:53.520 --> 31:55.870
I COULDN'T HELP
THINKING WHERE...

31:57.785 --> 32:00.527
WHERE WAS MY LIFEGUARD
WHEN I NEEDED HIM?

32:00.657 --> 32:01.832
-IT WAS MIDNIGHT.

32:02.572 --> 32:04.923
-IT WAS THE LAST NIGHT
I SPENT IN THIS HOUSE.

32:08.535 --> 32:10.319
AND FOR OVER 30 YEARS,

32:10.450 --> 32:13.714
I'VE WAITED FOR SOMEONE
TO COME AND KNOCK ON THE DOOR...

32:15.498 --> 32:16.630
AND ASK ME ABOUT THAT NIGHT.

32:17.718 --> 32:18.588
-NO, IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

32:20.460 --> 32:21.809
-WHEN YOU'RE A MOVIE STAR...

32:23.115 --> 32:24.290
THERE ARE NO ACCIDENTS.

32:25.117 --> 32:27.510
ONLY SCANDAL, THAT'S ALL
THE PUBLIC REMEMBERS.

32:29.904 --> 32:31.427
AT LEAST I AVOIDED THAT.

32:32.211 --> 32:34.735
-I GUESS SO. YOU LOCKED YOURSELF
AWAY FOR THREE DECADES.

32:35.562 --> 32:36.693
-WASN'T SO BAD.

32:38.130 --> 32:40.871
THE MORE I STAYED OUT
OF THE PUBLIC EYE, THE MORE
THEY TALKED ABOUT ME.

32:45.528 --> 32:48.096
DID YOU INJURE YOUR LEG
SAVING SOMEONE'S LIFE?

32:48.923 --> 32:51.012
-MY HIP, YES.

32:53.406 --> 32:55.234
-WHAT A MOVIE THIS WOULD MAKE.

32:55.364 --> 32:56.800
[LAUGHING]

32:56.931 --> 33:00.152
NOT TODAY, GOD FORBID,
BUT A CLASSIC MOVIE.

33:00.979 --> 33:02.981
THE LIFEGUARD HERO

33:03.546 --> 33:08.334
AND THE MOVIE QUEEN REUNITED
AFTER 30 STAR-CROSSED YEARS.

33:08.464 --> 33:10.814
[LAUGHS]

33:13.556 --> 33:15.036
HOW DO YOU THINK
IT WOULD END?

33:17.604 --> 33:19.388
-I HAVEN'T ANY IDEA.

33:19.519 --> 33:23.175
OH? WOULD THEY LET
THEIR GOLDEN OPPORTUNITY
PASS THEM BY

33:23.305 --> 33:25.438
AND LEAVE THE AUDIENCE
IN TEARS OR...

33:27.657 --> 33:29.311
OR WOULD THEY SEIZE THE MOMENT?

33:31.400 --> 33:33.011
AND SEND THE AUDIENCE
HOME ELATED...

33:34.882 --> 33:35.970
AND FULFILLED?

33:40.540 --> 33:42.368
-IF I HAD THE CHOICE...

33:42.498 --> 33:44.109
I'D TAKE THE FULFILLMENT.

33:45.197 --> 33:46.198
-SO WOULD I.

33:50.115 --> 33:51.551
BEN, YOU'RE BLUSHING.

33:51.681 --> 33:53.422
-NO, I GOT A LITTLE
SUNBURNED, THAT'S ALL.

33:54.075 --> 33:55.772
-BETTER PUT SOME LOTION ON.

33:55.903 --> 33:57.035
-SOME LOTION...

34:07.828 --> 34:11.266
-THIS IS K.M.F. 295,
SEND YOUR TRAFFIC 63-60.

34:11.397 --> 34:15.792
-ROGER. WE HAVE VISUAL
ON THE SUMO, HEADING SOUTHWEST
AT 10 KNOTS,

34:15.922 --> 34:17.880
THREE MILES SOUTH
OF LONG BEACH HARBOR.

34:18.012 --> 34:19.795
-10-4. THANKS
FOR THE ASSISTANCE.

34:19.927 --> 34:22.321
K.M.F. 295 TO RESCUE BAYWATCH.

34:22.451 --> 34:24.018
COAST GUARD RESPONDING.

34:24.149 --> 34:25.672
-GREAT, SHAUNI. THANK YOU.

34:25.802 --> 34:28.065
HEY, SEND THE COAST GUARD
MY LOVE, HUH?

34:28.978 --> 34:30.197
YOU FELLAS READY
TO GO FOR A RIDE?

34:30.893 --> 34:32.331
BETTER HANG ON
TO SOMETHING.

35:08.932 --> 35:11.021
-OKAY, JUST GET US
IN THERE FAST, EDDIE.

35:16.636 --> 35:18.203
STAY ON THE MOTHER SHIP!

35:18.333 --> 35:19.639
WE'VE GOT TO GET THERE
BEFORE THEY DUMP THOSE DRUGS.

35:30.867 --> 35:32.130
-WHAT HAPPENED?

35:32.260 --> 35:34.349
-NO GO. THEY TURNED
US DOWN COLD.

35:34.480 --> 35:36.917
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN? I THOUGHT
THE DEMONSTRATION WAS A SUCCESS.

35:37.047 --> 35:38.745
-IT WAS. WHAT CAN I TELL YOU?

35:39.354 --> 35:41.835
THEY STILL DON'T THINK
THE USE JUSTIFIES THE EXPENSE.

35:42.357 --> 35:44.446
-THOSE SHORT-SIGHTED, BLIND--

35:44.577 --> 35:46.622
-THIS IS K.M.F. 295
TO BAYWATCH DOCK.

35:46.753 --> 35:49.886
MITCH, EDDIE AND CONNORS
JUST FOUND THE DRUG LAB
ON A BOAT.

35:50.017 --> 35:52.280
8THEY'VE BEEN USING ADDICTORS
TO RUN THIS STUFF TO SHORE.

35:52.976 --> 35:54.369
MITCH, TWO OF THEM
ARE HEADED YOUR WAY.

35:57.546 --> 35:58.591
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

35:58.721 --> 36:00.158
-JUSTIFYING AN EXPENSE!

36:00.288 --> 36:02.247
-MITCH, THOSE AREN'T
APPROVED YET!

36:12.257 --> 36:13.780
IF YOU BREAK THEM,
DON'T BRING THEM BACK!

36:29.056 --> 36:30.666
♪

38:03.193 --> 38:05.500
[BOTH SHOUTING]

38:05.631 --> 38:06.632
-AH!

38:29.481 --> 38:30.743
-HOBIE'S VOICE:
DAD, WATCH OUT!

38:31.352 --> 38:32.745
DAD, BEHIND YOU!

38:42.711 --> 38:43.843
-YEAH!

39:00.990 --> 39:02.078
-IT'S STRANGE, HOBIE.

39:03.863 --> 39:04.733
IT'S LIKE...

39:05.299 --> 39:06.169
-WHAT?

39:08.346 --> 39:10.130
-I NEVER SAW
THE ADDICTOR COMING.

39:11.392 --> 39:12.915
I MEAN, I NEVER
EVEN HEARD IT.

39:15.135 --> 39:16.745
SUDDENLY I HEAR YOU
YELLING, "DAD!

39:17.442 --> 39:19.095
WATCH OUT, LOOK OUT
BEHIND YOU!"

39:19.748 --> 39:21.010
-LIKE IN MY DREAM.

39:21.141 --> 39:22.011
-YEAH.

39:23.665 --> 39:25.667
I DOVE OUT OF THE WAY
OF IT JUST IN TIME.

39:25.798 --> 39:27.016
-SEE, I TOLD YOU.

39:27.147 --> 39:29.062
-YEAH, YOU DID. YOU DID.

39:29.192 --> 39:30.368
-ALL RIGHT!

39:30.890 --> 39:32.979
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN, ALL RIGHT?

39:33.109 --> 39:35.373
-WELL, I HAD ANOTHER DREAM
ABOUT YOU GETTING MARRIED
LAST NIGHT.

39:35.982 --> 39:36.852
-YOU DID?

39:37.505 --> 39:38.376
TO WHO?

39:39.159 --> 39:40.813
-I DON'T KNOW, BUT
SHE SURE WAS PRETTY.

39:40.943 --> 39:41.944
-THAT'S GOOD.

39:42.858 --> 39:44.033
WAS SHE A BLOND
OR A BRUNETTE?

39:44.947 --> 39:45.818
-BLOND.

39:46.558 --> 39:48.298
-SHE DIDN'T SAY HER NAME, HUH?

39:48.429 --> 39:50.605
-NO, BUT I'LL TRY
AND DREAM ABOUT HER
AGAIN TONIGHT.

39:51.345 --> 39:52.390
-WELL, IF YOU DO,

39:53.478 --> 39:54.435
COME AND WAKE ME UP.

39:54.566 --> 39:55.654
-WHY?

39:56.263 --> 39:57.177
-WELL...

39:57.917 --> 40:00.136
YOUR DREAMS SOUND LIKE
THEY'RE A LOT BETTER THAN MINE.

40:02.051 --> 40:04.837
[PLAYFUL NOISES]

40:04.967 --> 40:05.751
YOU'RE IT!

40:05.881 --> 40:06.926
AH!

40:12.671 --> 40:13.933
AH!
